• Editor's note: This live event has ended. You may watch a recording above. JOHANNESBURG - Day two of load-shedding continues to weigh down the economy. On Wednesday, the power utility was forced to impose load-shedding for the first time in around seven months. READ: Eskom apologises for load-shedding Eskom's acting CEO Jabu Mabuza is expected to provide information on the current electricity supply challenges and recovery plans. The power cuts also affected supplies to Zimbabwe, where Eskom exports up to 400 MW daily. - Additional reporting Reuters